text: Been working on a small project and I'd like some input before I print it. Y'all familar with the "sheriff" multiplayer variant? BANG but as a commander game?

Mostly right now I'm looking for things that don't make sense, are spelled wrong, weird formatting, what have you

Nah just printing in color and putting in a sleeve with a regular card
I'll use different-color sleeves for the alternate Marchesa and Bragos I think, just to distinguish that they're not Starting roles
Honestly, I'd ditch the reveal reminder text...I don't think it adds enough and the wording's a little awkward.

Yeah it looks like really solid gimp or photoshop work. Great job.
man, gimp job sounds dirty
Another concern is the Usurper. I worry it might read a little awkwardly
it should be “when”
Something to that effect.
On Kaya's card I don't like the reminder text being at the same level as the main text.
I mean, it's a replacement effect, not a triggered ability. If you deal the killing blow and then something triggers, too late, the game is already over
Kaya's reminder text is another thing. We've had problems with formatting it
then drop the would in the first row “if you deliever the killing blow”
I dunno man, every replacement effect in the game uses the word 'would'
That implies this uses the stack...
Replacement effects don't use the stack
I dunno, it's all basically nitpicks at this point. I just wanted another set of eyes on them to make sure I didn't miss anything
I think the real culprit might be the phrase “deliver the killing blow” as it doesn’t really say what it means
It's supremely vague for sure. I don't know a Magic-y way to phrase it
yeah
It's kinda like Mathas in that way. There's not really a way to do it the way people actually wanted
(where just you and the person who destroyed the Bounty'd creature get the reward. There's no simple Magic-y way to phrase that)
“if you would destroy a player with the role of”
if you would deliever a sick burn
Another nitpick is "when you defeat the ruler." Initially that was "When the ruler is defeated" but I felt that was too passive

The worry being that a player might assume that as an Agitator they themselves have to be the one who deals the final blow to the king to win. I figured since "defeat" was such an arbitrary term it would be fine, though. Just a blanket term for "outlive"

Already flipped and ready to be printed on transparency. My hi-res transparencies will be ready for pickup tomorrow. You're more than welcome to use my pdf's and save yourself the trouble. Then you just need some spray adhesive and some blank foils.
Before anyone asks, they are backwards because you want the ink side to be "in" facing the card so that the image doesn't get scratched. It protects the ink so that the non-inked side is exposed.
